objects.moduledoc: This module handles fetching values from the config with some additional niceties

objects.name: get
objects.doc:
GET http method without request body.

  * `conn` - `%Maxwell.Conn{}`

Returns `{:ok, %Maxwell.Conn{}}` or `{:error, reason_term, %Maxwell.Conn{}}`.

objects.name: get!
objects.doc:
GET! http method without request body.

  * `conn` - see `get/1`

Returns `%Maxwell.Conn{}` or raise `%MaxWell.Error{}` when status not in [200..299].

objects.name: get!
objects.doc:
GET! http method without request body.

   * `conn` - see `get/1`
   * `normal_statuses` - the specified status which not raise exception, for example: [200, 201]

Returns `%Maxwell.Conn{}` or raise `%MaxWell.Error{}`.

objects.name: post!
objects.doc:
POST! http method.

   * `conn` - see `post/1`

Return `%Maxwell.Conn{}` or raise `%Maxwell.Error{}` when status not in [200.299]

objects.name: post!
objects.doc:
POST! http method.

  * `conn` - see `post/1`
  * `normal_statuses` - the specified status which not raise exception, for example: [200, 201]

Returns `%Maxwell.Conn{}` or raise `%MaxWell.Error{}`.

objects.name: get
objects.doc:
Fetches a value from the config, or from the environment if {:system, "VAR"}
is provided.

An optional default value can be provided if desired.

## Example

    iex> {test_var, expected_value} = System.get_env |> Enum.take(1) |> List.first
    ...> Application.put_env(:myapp, :test_var, {:system, test_var})
    ...> ^expected_value = Elixir.Telex.Config.get(:myapp, :test_var)
    ...> :ok
    :ok

    iex> Application.put_env(:myapp, :test_var2, 1)
    ...> 1 = Elixir.Telex.Config.get(:myapp, :test_var2)
    1

    iex> :default = Elixir.Telex.Config.get(:myapp, :missing_var, :default)
    :default

objects.name: get_integer
objects.doc:
Same as get/3, but returns the result as an integer.
If the value cannot be converted to an integer, the
default is returned instead.
